SIMPLE: remonstrance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remonstrance
<hw>Re*mon"strance</hw> <pr>(-m?n"str<it>a</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. OF. <ets>remonstrance</ets>, F. <ets>remonstrance</ets>. See
<er>Remonstrate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
remonstrating</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A pointing out;
manifestation; proof; demonstration.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You may marvel why I . . . would not rather⟦br⟧
Make rash <qex>remonstrance</qex> of my hidden power⟦br⟧
Than let him be so lost.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Earnest presentation of reason in opposition to
something; protest; expostulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R.C.Ch.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Monstrance</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remonstrant</ent>⟦br⟧
